        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued September 12 at 1:27PM MDT by NWS Grand Junction CO</headline>
        <description>At 127 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 24
miles east of Green River, moving northeast at 30 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and nickel size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation and
outdoor objects is possible.

This storm will remain over mainly rural areas of central Grand
County.

This includes Interstate 70 in Utah between mile markers 185 and 193.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
